<TITLE> Play proactive roles to control law and order: PM to DCs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 28 (bdnews24.com)  Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has asked deputy commissioners to play proactive roles to keep law and order situation under control and to uproot militancy. Addressing the inauguration of a three-day council of deputy commissioners on Tuesday, the prime minister placed emphasis transparency, accountability, skill and professionalism for an efficient service-based administration. She said "no excuses" would be entertained for shortcomings in these areas. "If you face any trouble while executing your duties with honesty and determination then the government will be behind you," she told the officials representing 64 districts. Tuesday marked the first formal council of DC's since the new government came to power in January. Around 300 topics will come up for discussion during the three-day conference, say officials. "The DCs will discuss the problems of the administration at the grassroots level," cabinet secretary Abdul Aziz told bdnews24.com. "There will be exchange of views on leasing out water bodies, dealing with vested property, Khas lands, land acquisition and the speed of development at the field level," he said. Separate sessions will be held with different ministries, he said. President Zillur Rahman will address the council on Wednesday afternoon at Bangabhaban. The start of the council was delayed because of inclement weather and water logging resulting from heavy overnight rains. bdnews24
